I"l<p>We are a theoretical research group at the <a href="https://chem.cst.temple.edu">Temple University Dept of Chemistry</a>. The focus of our group is to develop and apply theoretical methods to study nonadiabatic phenomena and their potential implications.  Focus areas are: Photophysics and photochemistry of biologically relevant systems, such as DNA/RNA; Theoretical description of conical intersections and excited states; Understanding laser control of molecular dynamics.</p>

